   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CELEBRATING CHRISTMAS DAY IN TEARS - SADNESS - WITHOUT SHESLTER On December  22, 2019 -- At least 15 persons died including children,   over 30 others were injured  and hundreds of homes destroyed  at a neighborhood in Burundi&apos;s commercial capital Bujumbura,  flooding caused by Saturday night&apos;s heavy rains. The location that has been more destroyed and affected by the torrential floods is called  &quot;Winterekwa&quot;. Today in this location and  surrounding areas there are tears and sadness of survivors</narrative>
  </description>
